The idea behind the subnet as far as miner value proposition goes is that incentive is not simply in 73 emissions, it is also based on alleviating sell pressure on a ‘home’ subnet in which they hold tons of alpha

Example: A top miner of subnet X holds 200,000 alphas (a lot) and continues to mine for X alpha. To cover operating costs, if said miner sells alpha X rewards then there is constant sell pressure on a pool in which they own a large amount of X alpha. 

This miner is in a position to leverage MetaHash. By offering their X alpha OTC to the treasury, they are rewarded with *liquidity to cover their operational costs*. The miner does this without impacting the value of their 200,000 alphas. Over time, utilizing this OTC strategy, their 200,000 alphas stand better ground to appreciate compared to if they were dumping their own alpha X emissions on themselves.

I hope this example better illustrates the intended purpose of this subnet for miners. Incentive is not scoped exclusively to 73’s emissions, it is also conditional to your operations on your home subnet.
